Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of self-backhauled mm-wave cellular networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses signal to interference plus noise ratio distribution and mean rates, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with millimeter wave cellular networks, which are used for high-speed data transmission, a topic related to multimedia. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes different access-backhaul and UL-DL resource allocation schemes, which are related to system design and control. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the societal impact of mm-wave cellular networks and their deployment.
